\int_{0}^{2}\frac{t-1}{\sqrt{a^2+b^2-2ab(t-1)}}dt~~(0<a<b)
I=\int_{0}^{2}\frac{t-1}{\sqrt{a^2+b^2-2ab(t-1)}}dt~~(0<a<b)
t-1=u
I=\int_{-1}^1\frac{u}{\sqrt{a^2+b^2-2abu}}du~~(0<a<b)
a^2+b^2-2abu=v^2,
\displaystyle  u=\frac{a^2+b^2-v^2}{2ab}
\displaystyle du=-\frac {vdv}{ab}
I=-\frac1{2a^2b^2}\int_{b+a}^{b-a}\frac{a^2+b^2-v^2}{v}vdv~~(0<a<b)
2a^2b^2\cdot I=\int_{b-a}^{b+a}(a^2+b^2-v^2)dv~~(0<a<b)
=(a^2+b^2)v\big |_{b-a}^{b+a}-\frac{v^3 \big |_{b-a}^{b+a}}3
=(a^2+b^2)\{(b+a)-(b-a)\}-\frac{(b+a)^3-(b-a)^3}3
=2a(a^2+b^2)-\frac{2a(3b^2+a^2)}3=\frac{2a\{3(a^2+b^2)-(3b^2+a^2)\}}3=\frac{4a^3}3 
\implies I=\frac{\frac{4a^3}3}{2a^2b^2}=\frac{2a}{3b^2}
